FINANCE minister Mthuli Ncube will on Monday headline the Associated Newspapers of Zimbabwe (ANZ) webinar on the 2020 Mid-Term Budget Review which he delivered on Thursday. ANZ are the publishers of the inimitable Daily News and the Daily News On Sunday. The discussion will be live streamed on the Daily News Facebook page on Monday at 8.30am. The highly anticipated webinar, to be moderated by prominent lawyer, Nqobile Munzara, will feature Confederation of Zimbabwe Industries (CZI) president Henry Ruzvidzo, Bankers Association of Zimbabwe vice president, Ron Mutandagayi, Chamber of Mines of Zimbabwe (CoMZ) Chief Executive Officer Isaac Kwesu, Confederation of Zimbabwe Retailers (CZR) president Denford Mutashu and SME Association of Zimbabwe (SMEAZ) founding chairman, Farai Mutambanengwe. ANZ commercial director Lewis Chikurunhe, said the webinar would present business leaders, decision-makers and ordinary citizens the opportunity to get more details on the 2020 Mid-Term Budget Review. “All are welcome to follow proceedings on the Daily News Facebook on Monday morning,” said Chikurunhe.   